<subSubSection id="C35C48E8FFAFFFD3F4CCFF52FCF4A2A3" box="[136,828,158,185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCFF52FCF4A2A3" blockId="2.[136,828,158,185]" box="[136,828,158,185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<taxonomicName id="4C4660E0FFAFFFD3F4CCFF52FE79A2A3" authorityName="Al-Shehbaz, Warwick, Mumm. &amp; M.Koch" authorityYear="2010" box="[136,433,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="240" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Microlepidieae">
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F4CCFF52FEC8A2A3" box="[136,256,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Arabidella</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F572FF52FE79A2A3" box="[310,433,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Lemphoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily separated as follows:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35C48E8FFAFFFD3F4CCFF2FFA62A355" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" type="key">
<keyStep id="30B203C6FFAFFFD3F4CCFF2FFA62A355" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<key id="FFD74C52FFAFFFD3F4CCFF2FFA62A355" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCFF2FFA63A30F" blockId="2.[136,1452,227,335]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCFF2FFA63A30F" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
1a. Shrubs or subshrubs, rarely annual herbs; lower leaves 2-, 3- or rarely multisect into linear to filiform lobes; nectar glands confluent, median glands present; ovules 20–90 per ovary; fruits linear, subterete or slightly latiseptate .......................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C4660E0FFAFFFD3F101FF33FA63A30F" authorityName="Schulz" authorityYear="1924" baseAuthorityName="Mueller" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[1349,1451,255,276]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabidella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F101FF33FA63A30F" box="[1349,1451,255,276]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Arabidella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCFED0FA62A355" blockId="2.[136,1452,227,335]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCFED0FA62A355" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
1b. Annual herbs; lower leaves pinnatifid to pinnatisect; nectar glands lateral, not confluent, median glands absent; ovules 6–70 per ovary; fruits oblong to linear siliques, or elliptic to suborbicular silicles, subterete or angustiseptate.............................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4660E0FFAFFFD3F105FEF5FA62A355" authorityName="Schulz" authorityYear="1924" box="[1345,1450,313,334]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lemphoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F105FEF5FA62A355" box="[1345,1450,313,334]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Lemphoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</key>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
